main event: A radar detection of an unidentified flying object near Blackwood, New Jersey on August 29, 1950
interesting points: The sighting was reported by a civilian source and lasted for 5 minutes.
The report card indicates there was only 1 object detected on radar.
The conclusion stated on the report card was 'Insufficient data for analysis'.
The report was forwarded to the Aerospace Technical Intelligence Center for further evaluation and analysis.
The letter acknowledges receipt of the report and indicates a questionnaire was attached for the witness to complete.
